The article is a transcript of a speech given by the President of the United States before signing the HIRE Act, a law aimed at promoting job creation and helping Americans who are unemployed. The President also briefly discusses the ongoing debate on healthcare reform and highlights the positive impact of the HIRE Act on small businesses and the economy. He emphasizes the need for further measures to stimulate private sector growth and address the challenges faced by the middle class. The President commends the bipartisan support for the HIRE Act and expresses his commitment to fighting for the American people. The article concludes with the signing of the law.